column1: #Text=# [ICRA 2024] Benchmarking Classical and Learning-Based Multibeam Point Cloud Registration*
#Text=The data is now released and can be found [here](https://kth-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/liling_ug_kth_se/EpXHLtknBFVIpvBIdMcNSOMBu8SPQIOt7tUNeUvQwB-O8g?
#Text=### [Benchmarking Classical and Learning-Based Multibeam Point Cloud Registration](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2405.06279)
#Text=|<sup>1</sup>KTH Royal Institute of Technology|<sup>2</sup>TU Graz|<sup>3</sup>Ocean Infinity|<sup>4</sup>University of Gothenburg|
#Text=For more information, please check out the [project website](https://luxiya01.github.io/mbes-registration-project-page/)
#Text=If you have any questions, feel free to contact us at:
#Text=This repository contains the implementation for the MBES Dataset class and data loader, the classical methods GICP and FPFH, as well as the code for metrics computation and evaluations.
#Text=The code use to run the learning-based models are found in the following repository forks:
#Text=The dataset, pretrained models and evaluation results can be found [here](https://kth-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/liling_ug_kth_se/EpXHLtknBFVIpvBIdMcNSOMBu8SPQIOt7tUNeUvQwB-O8g?
#Text=Note that the dataset only contains the patches segmented according to the paper description.
#Text=To construct a registration dataset, please consult [main.py](https://github.com/luxiya01/mbes-registration-data/blob/main/src/main.py).
#Text=If you want the exact data pairs and transforms as used in the paper, you can also extract these from the _npz_ files containing in each method's evaluation results.
#Text=If you find this code useful for your work, please consider citing:
#Text=            title={Benchmarking Classical and Learning-Based Multibeam Point Cloud Registration},
#Text=            author={Ling, Li and Zhang, Jun and Bore, Nils and Folkesson, John and Wåhlin, Anna},
#Text=            booktitle={2024 IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation (ICRA)},
